HoloNoGraSeasonOneAnimeData.Sypnosis: From unraveling the secrets of opening and closing doors to defusing surprise packages more commonly known as bombs, there is never a dull day at the Hololive Production office! Holo no Graffiti follows an eccentric cast of Virtual YouTubers, also known as "VTubers," going about their absurd yet hilarious daily lives, detailing all their cute moments and mishaps.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Tokino Sora
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: She is an easy-going, happy, and comforting person whose personality has led many fans to call her 'Sora Mama' because of her motherly attitude. She also has a playful side to her, with an example being that she has put on a horse head while streaming a game. She is also a bit carefree as she does not mind revealing her age and weight on stream in contrast to other hololive members.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Hoshimachi Suisei
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A cheerful shining Idol and Vtuber from Hololive 0th Generation. She is a forever 18, multitalented girl who deeply loves singing and idols, with the dream of one day holding a live concert in Tokyo Budokan. She started out as an independent Vtuber and later joined Inonaka Music, a music label under Hololive, before moving officially to Hololive main branch.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Sakura Miko
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: She has been working on religious services really hard as a miko in the computer world. With the revelation of the gods, she is now visiting Japan. While performing her errand, she has now decided to become and work hard as a virtual miko idol.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Roboco
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A lonely, wimpy robot from a random wasteland. She is now hoping to contact and live with lots of people as a Virtual Liver.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Yozora Mel
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A vampire girl. Even though she is a vampire, she is not into blood. She loves acerola juice quite a lot.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Shirakami Fubuki
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A white haired kemomimi highschool student. Although she is shy and mostly calm, she likes to talk to people. She would be very happy if you pay attention to her.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Natsuiro Matsuri
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A rookie on the Cheerleading Team. Cheerful and affectionate, her pleasant attitude means she gets along with everyone. She has a lot of friends, and loves festivals and events.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Aki Rosenthal
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A girl who traveled from a different universe. She has hyper curiosity and manages to reach out to all sorts of things. Her trademark pigtails float due to some sort of supernatural power.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Akai Haato
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A sassy kouhai. She is often prickly, however she manages to demand lots of attention from those with whom she has been getting along well. She loves red ribbons and heart shapes.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Yuzuki Choco
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A health doctor from the Demonic-Realm Academy. Has a high reputation around the school. It was told that the line of male students never ends. She loves snacks quite a lot, although one time her desk was caked with food wrappers, and she was then scolded badly.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Oozora Subaru
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: The manager of an MMA club and an E-sports club. A supremely spirited, cheerful, lively girl who can talk to anyone without breaking a sweat. She’s currently practicing her pro-gamer skills.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Nakiri Ayame
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A kimono-clad Oni girl from the Demonic-Realm Academy. As she loves to prank people, she always uses will-o’-the-wisp on them just to have fun. Many may not realize it, but she is actually the president of the student council.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Murasaki Shion
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A random self-proclaimed child who appears around the Demonic-Realm Academy. She calls herself a highborne black magician.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Minato Aqua
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A marine maid-styled virtual maid. She is trying her very best, yet is still sometimes awkward and clumsy.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Ookami Mio
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A black haired kemomimi girl who appeared on our radar randomly. She often shows up around shrines. She likes gaming.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Nekomata Okayu
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A cat raised by a old woman from the onigiri store. She streams just because there is a PC in the old woman’s room.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Inugami Korone
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: The dog from a random bakery. She likes to play games when she has free time while watchdogging.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Usada Pekora
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A lonely rabbit-eared girl who loves carrots. She loves them so much that she always brings a few anywhere she goes.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Uruha Rushia
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A necromancer from the Demonic-Realm Academy who is not good at communicating with people. She does not want to be alone, however, which is why she talks to the spirits and the damned.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Shiranui Flare
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A half-elf who seems sloppy and undependable, however when it is time, she becomes an extremely reliable big sis.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Shirogane Noel
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: While she is easy-going, she has a dangerous side where she attempts to solve all her problems with muscle power. As much as this fluffy, meatheaded knight hungers for power, she came to the world of VTubers where all the stronk people are, for training.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Houshou Marine
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: Loves jewels, treasure, and money. Her dream is to become a pirate and go treasure hunting. In order to get a pirate ship, she is now stacking up money as a VTuber on the great lands, just like how the other land-lovers do

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Himemori Luna
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: The princess of sweets. She sticks around people, and is easily impressed. However, when her childishness overloads, she will get scolded by her butler. It was also told that those moonshapes are the symbols of her country.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Tokoyami Towa
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: Towa-sama is a devil that's terrible at being a devil.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Tsunomaki Watame
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A sheep bard that goes around everywhere. She loves singing and is fluffy! YES! FLUFFY! Being a herbivore, she loves potato chips.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Kiryu Coco
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: Coco is a lively Yakuza dragon that loves crude humor. She's a strong, openhearted, and honest person who loves making friends with other members of hololive. Additionally, Coco is the host of her own satiric news show, Asacoco.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Amane Kanata
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: An angel from the Angelic-Realm Institution. She is now studying how to heal people.To hide her shyness, she pretends to be cool.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Yukihana Lamy
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: A snow elf from a noble family renowned in the remote Land of Silver. She decided to leave her home, along with her companion Daifuku, after her heart was touched by the fun and colorful streams from hololive. Her serious personality belies her naive, sheltered nature.

HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Name: Omaru Polka
HoloNoGraSeasonOneCharacterData.Description: Japanese Virtual YouTuber associated with hololive, as part of its fifth generation of VTubers. A circus performer who joined hololive in hopes of becoming the ringmaster of the VTuber world. She enjoys wowing audiences with acrobatics, and lives by the words, 'When the going gets tough, the tough get going.' If you ask her, her occasional mess ups are also part of her charm.

JJBASeasonOneAnimeData.Sypnosis: In 1868, Dario Brando saves the life of an English nobleman, George Joestar. By taking in Dario's son Dio when the boy becomes fatherless, George hopes to repay the debt he owes to his savior. However Dio, unsatisfied with his station in life, aspires to seize the Joestar house for his own. Wielding an Aztec stone mask with supernatural properties, he sets out to destroy George and his son, Jonathan "JoJo" Joestar, and triggers a chain of events that will continue to echo through the years to come.

JJBASeasonTwoAnimeData.Sypnosis: Years after an ancient evil was salvaged from the depths of the sea, Joutarou Kuujou sits peacefully within a Japanese jail cell. He's committed no crime yet demands he not be released, believing he's been possessed by an evil spirit capable of harming those around him. Concerned for her son, Holly Kuujou asks her father, Joseph Joestar, to convince Joutarou to leave the prison. Joseph informs his grandson that the "evil spirit" is in fact something called a "Stand," the physical manifestation of one's fighting spirit which can adopt a variety of deadly forms. After a fiery brawl with Joseph's friend Mohammed Avdol, Joutarou is forced out of his cell and begins learning how to control the power of his Stand.However, when a Stand awakens within Holly and threatens to consume her in 50 days, Joutarou, his grandfather, and their allies must seek out and destroy the immortal vampire responsible for her condition. They must travel halfway across the world to Cairo, Egypt and along the way, do battle with ferocious Stand users set on thwarting them. If Joutarou and his allies fail in their mission, humanity is destined for a grim fate.

JJBASeasonThreeAnimeData.TitleName: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Stardust Crusaders - Battle in Egypt
JJBASeasonThreeAnimeData.Sypnosis: Joutarou Kuujou and his allies have finally made it to Egypt, where the immortal Dio awaits. Upon their arrival, the group gains a new comrade: Iggy, a mutt who wields the Stand "The Fool." It's not all good news however, as standing in their path is a new group of Stand users who serve Dio, each with a Stand representative of an ancient Egyptian god. As their final battle approaches, it is a race against time to break Joutarou's mother free from her curse and end Dio's reign of terror over the Joestar family once and for all.

JJBASeasonFourAnimeData.TitleName: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Diamond is Unbreakable
JJBASeasonFourAnimeData.Sypnosis: The year is 1999. Morioh, a normally quiet and peaceful town, has recently become a hotbed of strange activity. Joutarou Kuujou, now a marine biologist, heads to the mysterious town to meet Jousuke Higashikata. While the two may seem like strangers at first, Jousuke is actually the illegitimate child of Joutarou's grandfather, Joseph Joestar. When they meet, Joutarou realizes that he may have more in common with Jousuke than just a blood relation.

JJBASeasonFiveAnimeData.Sypnosis: In the coastal city of Naples, corruption is teeming—the police blatantly conspire with outlaws, drugs run rampant around the youth, and the mafia governs the streets with an iron fist. However, various fateful encounters will soon occur.

JJBASeasonSixAnimeData.Sypnosis: In Florida, 2011, Jolyne Kuujou sits in a jail cell like her father Joutarou once did; yet this situation is not of her own choice. Framed for a crime she didn’t commit, and manipulated into serving a longer sentence, Jolyne is ready to resign to a dire fate as a prisoner of Green Dolphin Street Jail. Though all hope seems lost, a gift from Joutarou ends up awakening her latent abilities, manifesting into her Stand, Stone Free. Now armed with the power to change her fate, Jolyne sets out to find an escape from the stone ocean that holds her.
